Basic structure of Function

my_function &lt;- function(argument1, argument2) {
    result &lt;- code that does something
    return(result)
}

Write a R Function


add_numbers &lt;- function(x, y) {
  result &lt;- x + y
  return(result)
}



function name - what we call it add_numbers()
An argument - what you give it function(x, y)
A body - what it does with it {result &lt;- x + y & return(result)}

Example 2 - Greet a participant

greet &lt;- function(name) {
  message &lt;- paste("Hello,", name, "!")
  return(message)
}

greet("Kiran")

[1] "Hello, Kiran !"

greet("Ajay")

[1] "Hello, Ajay !"

Example 4 — Classify a Score

classify_score &lt;- function(score) {
  if (score &gt;= 90) {
    return("Excellent")
  } else if (score &gt;= 75) {
    return("Good")
  } else if (score &gt;= 60) {
    return("Pass")
  } else {
    return("Needs Improvement")
  }
}

classify_score(92)

[1] "Excellent"

classify_score(78)

[1] "Good"

classify_score(55)

[1] "Needs Improvement"

